  <p>
    Replacing a septic system shares its bones with a new installation — soil evaluation, design,
    approvals, installation, restoration — but it carries extra weight a bare building lot never does.
    There's already a system in the ground, the property has a history of use, and the rules and
    standards may have moved since the original was put in. Those differences are what make
    replacement its own kind of project.
  </p>

  {/* Intended asset: /images/resources/replacing-an-older-septic-system-hero.webp — see public/images/resources/README.md */}
